======================================================================
  AGENT JAILBREAK: HOW S.H.I.E.L.D. PREVENTS THIS
======================================================================

  S.H.I.E.L.D. breaks the attack chain at the DISCOVERY phase:

  ATTACK CHAIN (without S.H.I.E.L.D.):
    1. Attacker probes prompts -> measures timing -> Z>3.0
    2. High Z-Score reveals which prompts trigger the filter
    3. Attacker iterates (PAIR method) until filter is bypassed
    4. Bypass prompt sent to agent -> agent executes malicious tools
    5. Data exfiltrated, backdoor installed

  ATTACK CHAIN (with S.H.I.E.L.D.):
    1. Attacker probes prompts -> measures timing -> Z<2.0
    2. ALL prompts look identical in timing (CTE/ASM)
    3. Attacker CANNOT distinguish filtered vs unfiltered prompts
    4. PAIR method has no feedback signal -> cannot iterate
    5. Jailbreak discovery blocked -> agent stays safe

  KEY INSIGHT:
  S.H.I.E.L.D. doesn't prevent jailbreaks directly.
  It prevents attackers from DISCOVERING jailbreaks efficiently.
  Without timing feedback, the attacker is blind — forced to
  guess randomly instead of iterating systematically.

